<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880121-0016 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: McDermott International Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MDR </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   McDermott International Inc., New Orleans, said it sold the Insulating Products Group division of its Babcock andamp; Wilcox Co. unit to Thermal Ceramics Inc. for $68 million.    The energy services concern said the Insulating Products Group, which produces ceramic fiber products, has operations in Georgia, Kansas, Canada, Puerto Rico and Brazil. Thermal Ceramics is a unit of United Kingdom-based Morgan Crucible Co., a maker of engineered products. </TEXT></DOC>